00:46:52,636 --> 00:46:57,618
And we spent a lot of time talking with our artist Kyle Farrin about how we were going

953
00:46:57,638 --> 00:46:58,739
to go about presenting it.

954
00:46:59,299 --> 00:47:03,100
And early on, we kind of arrived at a strategy, which was...

955
00:47:04,376 --> 00:47:07,038
So there are sort of two problems with introductory war games.

956
00:47:07,778 --> 00:47:11,821
Problem one is introductory war games play nothing like actual war games.

957
00:47:11,861 --> 00:47:14,443
And I think Blood Rage is quite instructive here, right?

958
00:47:14,463 --> 00:47:15,664
Like Blood Rage is a drafting game.

959
00:47:16,524 --> 00:47:20,867
It's not a war game, I think, in any kind of meaningful sense, and I don't think anybody

960
00:47:21,648 --> 00:47:22,408
– that's a bit of a straw man.

961
00:47:22,428 --> 00:47:23,849
I don't think anybody would necessarily defend that.

962
00:47:25,487 --> 00:47:26,908
So that's problem one, right?

963
00:47:26,928 --> 00:47:29,471
So we wanted to make sure that if this was an introductory game,

964
00:47:29,731 --> 00:47:32,614
that it was actually going to show people

965
00:47:32,675 --> 00:47:34,076
what the other games looked like.

966
00:47:34,517 --> 00:47:36,799
The other problem that introductory games have

967
00:47:37,039 --> 00:47:40,703
is that they try to bring people into the hobby,

968
00:47:40,904 --> 00:47:45,368
but they do it in a way that isn't actually that accessible.

969
00:47:45,429 --> 00:47:47,571
So Blood Rage has really intense art.

970
00:47:48,380 --> 00:47:50,502
It's just a lot of like blood and brawny guys.

