to keep the players even if they are losing.

1220
00:59:27,542 --> 00:59:30,465
So you're asking specifically how do we take

1221
00:59:30,485 --> 00:59:32,186
some of these lessons into the video game space?

1222
00:59:33,167 --> 00:59:34,849
It could be also for tabletop games.

1223
00:59:34,909 --> 00:59:37,471
It's like how you encourage this emerging storytelling

1224
00:59:37,511 --> 00:59:39,113
as a way of keeping engagement.

1225
00:59:39,431 --> 00:59:41,912
Yeah, so I think that in general, and we're just out of time,

1226
00:59:41,952 --> 00:59:44,552
but I have a short but I think good answer to this question,

1227
00:59:44,592 --> 00:59:47,733
which is to say what you're doing when you are doing game design

1228
00:59:47,773 --> 00:59:50,774
is you're giving players a language to exist in the world.

1229
00:59:51,294 --> 00:59:54,395
And you have to pay a lot of attention to how that language is built,

1230
00:59:54,495 --> 00:59:56,275
because some languages are going to be quite restrictive

1231
00:59:56,715 --> 00:59:58,055
in the stories that you're allowing them to tell,

1232
00:59:58,115 --> 00:59:59,676
and other languages can be quite capacious.

1233
00:59:59,696 --> 01:00:03,897
And I think a good example of this is something like Fantasy Flight's Netrunner.

1234
01:00:04,257 --> 01:00:05,397
When Netrunner first came out,

1235
01:00:05,877 --> 01:00:07,018
It was easy to make fun of the fact

1236
01:00:07,038 --> 01:00:08,519
that they were calling actions clicks

1237
01:00:08,579 --> 01:00:10,840
and they had invented this funny little dialect

1238
01:00:10,880 --> 01:00:11,780
to talk about their game.

1239
01:00:12,320 --> 01:00:15,442
But what it did is it immersed players in the world

1240
01:00:15,462 --> 01:00:17,043
so that even when you were talking about Netrunner,

1241
01:00:17,063 --> 01:00:18,303
you were still playing Netrunner.

1242
01:00:18,704 --> 01:00:21,345
And so I think from the design perspective,

1243
01:00:21,865 --> 01:00:25,147
give your players a language that is as expressive

1244
01:00:25,187 --> 01:00:27,768
as the game itself and really well-appointed

1245
01:00:27,808 --> 01:00:29,669
to talk about the world that you want them to exist in.

1246
01:00:29,689 --> 01:00:30,590
Okay, thank you very much.

1247
01:00:30,610 --> 01:00:31,310
Thank you for that question.

1248
01:00:31,350 --> 01:00:32,030
All right, and thank you guys

1249
01:00:32,070 --> 01:00:33,251
for all the questions and for coming.

